This sciprt is designed to visually inspect the coordinates from the
bsg_two padring to the bga package.

Software Requirements:

1. Python 3
2. ImageMagiks

Note: BB-39 has both of these installed

Repository Setup:

Please make sure that this repository is in the same directory as the
bsg_packaging repository.

Usage:

To generate the image type:

  $ make

The final image will end up in output/final.png. To view this image type:

  $ make display

The final image by default will be 2300x2300 pixels. There is a large scale
factor to make the image output 4600x4600. To output this large image type:

  $ make IMAGE_SCALE=200

--or--

  $ make IMAGE_SCALE=400


